As Keir Starmer signals boots on the ground in Ukraine and Labour slashes public spending to fund the war, we uncover the deeper story—how UK aid is fueling a fire sale of Ukraine’s economy. While the IMF and World Bank push mass privatisation, global financiers line up to carve up state assets. Is this really about defending democracy, or just another elite land grab? Then, Nicole Shanahan, once a key Democratic donor, reveals her political awakening.
